# PS Time Tracker

A time-tracking web app for Amplitude Professional Services, built by Giuliano Giannini (Senior Solutions Architect).

## Project Location

`~/Desktop/time-tracker`

## GitHub & Live Site

- Repo: https://github.com/GGFirenze/PSTimeTracker
- Live: https://ggfirenze.github.io/PSTimeTracker/

## Tech Stack

- React 18 + TypeScript + Vite
- LocalStorage for persistence (no backend)
- Amplitude Browser SDK via CDN script loader (PROD key `851e3783...` in `index.html`)
- Session Replay enabled (sampleRate: 1)
- Autocapture: pageViews, attribution, frustrationInteractions (others disabled)
- CSS (no framework) with CSS variables in `src/styles/index.css`
- Google Calendar embedded via iframe in `src/components/CalendarWidget.tsx`

## Architecture

- `src/context/ProjectContext.tsx` — dynamic project list (defaults + custom), persisted in LocalStorage
- `src/context/TimerContext.tsx` — timer state (start/pause/stop), time entries, persisted in LocalStorage
- `src/analytics.ts` — centralized Amplitude tracking helpers, uses `window.amplitude` from CDN
- `src/data/projects.ts` — default project definitions (10 billable + 4 non-billable)
- `src/components/CalendarWidget.tsx` — collapsible Google Calendar iframe

## Billable Customers

JPMC, Snyk, Pleo, ManoMano, Wallapop, Cabify, TheFork, Canal+, Doctolib, Fressnapf

## Non-Billable Categories

Internal Meetings, Internal Projects, Self Development, Free PS Hours

## Amplitude Events Tracked (9 custom events)

- Timer Started, Timer Paused, Timer Stopped (project_name, is_billable, duration_seconds)
- Note Viewed, Note Submitted (project_name, is_billable, note_text)
- Project Added, Project Deleted (project_name, is_billable)
- Calendar Opened, Calendar Collapsed

## Key Conventions

- Projects have `isDefault: true/false` — default projects cannot be deleted
- User-added projects show a delete (x) button with type-name-to-confirm safety modal
- Only one timer runs at a time; starting a new one auto-stops the previous
- Stopping a timer always shows the Notes modal for session notes
- All new Amplitude events should go through helpers in `src/analytics.ts`
- Color scheme: green = billable, crimson red = non-billable
- The dev server runs with `npm run dev` on `http://localhost:5173`

## Deployment

Hosted on GitHub Pages. To deploy changes:
```
npm run build && npx gh-pages -d dist
```
Vite base path is set to `/PSTimeTracker/` in `vite.config.ts`.
